name: Matthew Podszus
tweet: Quick post-script:  This interaction should basically never happened in front of the victim.   This version of advocacy and education should be performed in internationally conducive spaces for all parties, which are rarely together and seldom “on the fly.”

name: Matthew Podszus
tweet: 1) It’s likely a product of their own unresolved mistreatment or abuse, right?  2) Victim advocacy and intervention always aims at restoring a sense of agency. This matters.  3) We need to win people over to more balanced ways of seeing things. Scolding usually backfires.  3/3

name: Matthew Podszus
tweet: Sometimes people victim-blame because they’re concerned with victims not being deprived of an ongoing sense of agency. In many cases, this is what’s going on.  I wonder if, instead of scolding, we might emphasize that being a victim and retaining agency can go hand-in-hand.  1/3
